## Banned Patterns

- Hard-coding process type logic in ProcessesService (use registry)
- Bypassing state machine transitions (every status change must go through workflow.determineNextStep)
- Using Prisma raw SQL for display_id (use PostgreSQL sequence)
- Skipping transaction wrapping in multi-table writes
- Forgetting to emit events after state changes (notifications depend on this)
- Task completion without checking `claimed_by_user_id === actor.id`

